Street rave of the moment Portable has revealed the inspiration behind his decision to do music. According to the Nation, te controversial self-styled ‘wahala musician’ in a tweet said Wizkid’s popular hit song, “Ojuelegba” was the catalyst that propelled him to start doing music. “Wizkid’s Ojuelegba inspired me to start doing music”, he tweeted. However, his revelation sparked a debate on social media as many claimed even though Big Wiz still continues to inspire younger artistes to follow their dreams, he surely isn’t responsible for this one. Some said Portable’s inspiration ought to be Terry G. While others were more concerned about the person who tweeted noting Portable can’t write such English.         Singer Wizkid aka Big Wiz is celebrating the tenth anniversary of the release of his debut album, ‘Superstar’. For this, the Grammy award-winning star has dropped a documentary titled ‘A superstar made in Lagos’. The new documentary was released on Saturday, June 12, 2021. In the main video, Big Wiz… In "Entertainment" On Saturday, June 12, 2021, Grammy award-winning music star, Wizkid celebrated the 10th anniversary of his debut album ‘Superstar’. In a documentary shared on Wizkid’s Insastories, industry giants like Banky W, Ali Baba, Femi Kuti, Basketmouth, and others took turns to speak on the 30-year-old singer’s evolution since his successful… In "Entertainment" By Anita Eboigbe   Abuja    -       Afropop sensation, Ayodeji Balogun aka Wizkid pulled a show stopping sold-out show in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that thousands of Abuja residents thronged out in their numbers to see the show tagged ‘Wizkid Live In Concert’ held… In "Entertainment"